          <td class="mainbody">
<span class="headers">Trueshot Longbow Quest </span>
<p>
<h4>Created for EQTRaders by Gnormy Ahdairya of Terris-Thule </h4>
<p>Last updated: 7/11/2003</p>
<hr />
<p>Starts in Greater Faydark with Maesyn Trueshot at the Rangers Guild. 
It is suggested that you collect muliples of all materials.</p>


<h4>Minimum Materials Used for One Attempt </h4>
<hr />
<p>
1 Small Lantern<br />
1 Wooden Shards<br />
4 Flask of Water<br />
4 Kiola Nut<br />
4 Tumpy Tonic<br />
2 Dwarven Wire (no drop)<br />
2 Micro Servo (no drop)<br />
1 Spiderling Silk<br />
1 Materials Pack (no drop, lore, container)<br />
1 Pack of Materials (no drop, lore)<br />
1 Planing Tool<br />
1 Treant Bow Staff (lore)<br />
1 Fletching Kit (of any kind, container)
</p>
<h4>Overview</h4>
<hr />
<p>In West Freeport give Jyle Windshot 1 Small Lantern to recieve 1 Wooden Shards</p>
<p>In Ocean of Tears buy 4 Kiola Nut from Cleonae Kalen</p>
<p>In South Kaladim give Tumpy Irontoe 1 Flask of Water and 1 Kiola Nut to receive 1 Tumpy Tonic (do 4 times)<br />
OR Brew 1 Flask of Water + 1 Kiola Nut in Brew Barrel (of any type) to create 1 Tumpy Tonic (do 4 times)</p>
<p>In North Kaladim give Trantor Everhot 2 Tumpy Tonic (unstacked) to recieve 1 Dwarven Wire (do 2 times)</p>
<p>In SteamFont Mountains kill Rogue Clockwork and loot 1 Micro Servo (repeat until you have 2 Micro Servo)</p>
<p>In Greater Faydark tell Maesyn Trueshot "I will gather materials" to recieve Materials Pack (container)</p>
<p>Combine 1 Spiderling Silk + 1 Dwarven Wire + 1 Micro Servo + 1 Wooden Shards in Materials Pack to create Pack of Materials</p>
<p>Give Maesyn Trueshot Pack of Materials to recieve Treant Bow Staff</p>
<p>Fletch Treant Bow Staff + 1 Dwarven Wire + 1 Micro Servo + Planing Tool to create Trueshot Longbow (trival 235)</p>
<h4>Complete Walkthrough</h4>
<hr />
<p>You have entered Greater Faydark.<br />
Your Location is -451.03, 520.32, 116.28</p>
<blockquote><p>You say, 'Hail, Maesyn Trueshot'</p>
<p>Maesyn Trueshot says 'Welcome to Kelethin, Gnormy!  I am Maesyn Trueshot, commander of Faydark's Champions.  We are the finest marksmen in all of Norrath.  With our trusty [Trueshot longbows] we can miss no target regardless of the distance or the conditions.'</p>
<p>You say, 'what trueshot longbows'</p>
<p>Maesyn Trueshot says 'The Trueshot Longbow was created by my famed father, Eldin Trueshot. It is quite accurate and takes a ranger's skill to wield. We use our new recruits to [gather materials] needed by my father.  We shall soon begin to release the formula to good elves so all may fletch such a bow.'</p>
<p>You say, 'I will gather materials'</p>
<p>Maesyn Trueshot says 'Take this pack. Go to Kaladim, find Trantor Everhot and ask for dwarven wire. Then go to Freeport to meet Jyle Windshot. Search the inns for him and ask him for treant wood. Then, collect some spiderling silk from spiderlings and finally, in Steamfont, we have the permission of the gnomes to use any micro servos we find while destroying rogue spiders. Combine them all and return the pack to me.'</p>
</blockquote>
<p>[Recommended order is Freeport, OOT, Kaladim, Steamfont Moutains]</p>
<p>Plane of Knowledge</p>
<p>Peras Glickon tells you, 'That'll be 5 silver 2 copper for the Small Lantern.'</p>
<p>You give 5 silver 2 copper to Peras Glickon.</p>
<p>LOADING, PLEASE WAIT...</p>
<p>You have entered West Freeport.</p>
<blockquote><p>You say, 'Hail, Jyle Windshot'</p>
<p>Jyle Windshot says 'Hello.  Might I ask what you are looking for?'</p>
<p>[Note Jyle Windshot must con amibly or will not recieve reward - you can raise faction by doing muffin quest with Pandos in the hallway]</p>
<p>[Give Jyle Windwhot 1 Small Lantern]</p>
<p>Jyle Windshot says 'Thanks, friend.  I have run a long way to get here in time.  Mostly at night.  I lost my lantern in a card game in Highkeep.'</p>
<p>Your faction standing with Faydarks Champions got better. </p>
<p>Your faction standing with King Tearis Thex got better. </p>
<p>Your faction standing with Clerics of Tunare got better. </p>
<p>Your faction standing with Soldiers of Tunare got better. </p>
<p>Your faction standing with Crushbone Orcs got worse. </p>
<p>[Recieve 1 Wooden Shards from Jyle Windshot] </p>
</blockquote>
<p>LOADING, PLEASE WAIT... </p>
<p>You have entered Ocean of Tears.</p> 
<p>You say, 'Hail, Cleonae Kalen' </p>
<p>Cleonae Kalen says 'Welcome to the island of the Sisterhood of Erollisi.' </p>
<p>Cleonae Kalen tells you, 'That'll be 1 gold 7 silver 3 copper for the Kiola Nut.' </p>
<p>You give 1 gold 7 silver 3 copper to Cleonae Kalen. </p>
<p>Cleonae Kalen tells you, 'I'll give you 5 silver 2 copper for the Kiola Nut.' </p>
<p>[Note - you need 4 Kiola Nuts per attempt] </p>
<p>[Note - if you forget water like me, its available in North Kaladim near Cleric Guild]</p> 
<p>LOADING, PLEASE WAIT...</p> 
<p>You have entered North Kaladim. </p>
<p>Doramafi Ratsbone tells you, 'That'll be 1 silver per Water Flask.' </p>
<p>You give 2 gold to Doramafi Ratsbone. </p>
<p>LOADING, PLEASE WAIT... </p>
<p>You have entered South Kaladim. </p>
<p>Your Location is 182.37, 316.66, 4.88 </p>
<p>You say, 'Hail, Tumpy Irontoe' </p>
<p>Tumpy Irontoe says 'Welcome to Irontoe's! The finest watering hole this side of Oggok! If you're looking for anything special and it ain't behind the bar, just ask. Maybe I can make it.' </p>
<p>You say, 'I need a tumpy tonic'</p> 
<p>Tumpy Irontoe says 'So you want a Tumpy Tonic? I can make you one. All I need is a flask of water and a kiola nut. The kiola nut can be bought in the Ocean of Tears island chain.' </p>
<p>[Give Tumpy Irontoe 1 Flask of Water and 1 Kiola Nut] </p>
<p>Tumpy Irontoe says 'Okay. Where are the other ingredients?' </p>
<p>Tumpy Irontoe says 'Here you go. One Tumpy Tonic. Don't drink that too fast now.' </p>
<p>You gain experience!! </p>
<p>[Recieve 1 Tumpy Tonic from Tumpy Irontoe] </p>
<p>[Note - you will need 4 Tumpy Tonic to complete quest] </p>
<p>[Note - you can also brew the Tumpy Tonic yourself] </p>
<p>[Combine 1 Flask of Water and 1 Kiola Nut in a Brew Barrel] </p>
<p>[Brewing combine - Trivial = 1 Tumpy Tonic] </p>
<p>LOADING, PLEASE WAIT... </p>
<p>You have entered North Kaladim. </p>
<p>Your Location is 555.89, -276.99, 1.88 [Trantor wanders between several spots] </p>
<p>You say, 'Hail, Trantor Everhot' </p>
<p>Trantor Everhot says 'Yes, yes!! I am a very busy man. I've got blueprints to work on, [dwarven wire] to perfect and formulae to calculate. In between those tasks, I have to find time to head down to Irontoe's and down a few Tumpy Tonics.' </p>
<p>You say, 'what dwarven wire' </p>
<p>Trantor Everhot says 'Oh!! Interested in my dwarven wire, are you? Many are. I have no problem letting you use a spool, but I have to warn you that I have not perfected the strength of it yet. I will make you a trade. A couple of[Tumpy Tonics] for a spool.' </p>
<p>You say, 'what tumpy tonics' </p>
<p>Trantor Everhot says 'Aaah!! I love Tumpy Tonics. They were created by Tumpy Irontoe. He was once a member of the famed Irontoe Brigade. Since they disbanded and left for parts unknown he decided to stay in Kaladim and open Irontoe's, the finest well in Faydwer.' </p>
<p>[Give Trantor Everhot 2 Tumpy Tonic (unstacked)] </p>
<p>Trantor Everhot says 'Hey!! Only one?!!' </p>
<p>Gnormy saved. </p>
<p>Trantor Everhot says 'Great!! I did not have the time to get down to Irontoe's today. Here. Like I said. A spool of dwarven wire. Now go away. I ain't sharing these tonics.' </p>
<p>Your faction standing with Storm Guard got better. </p>
<p>Your faction standing with Kazon Stormhammer got better. </p>
<p>Your faction standing with Miners Guild 249 got better. </p>
<p>Your faction standing with Merchants of Kaladim got better. </p>
<p>Your faction standing with Craknek Warriors got worse. </p>
<p>You gain experience!! </p>
<p>[Recieve 1 Dwarven Wire] </p>
<p>[Note - you will need 2 Dwarven Wire so repeat this step] </p>
<p>LOADING, PLEASE WAIT... </p>
<p>You have entered Steamfont Mountains. </p>
<p>You have slain rogue clockwork! </p>
<p>rogue clockwork's corpse says 'This unit is terminally damaged..  Tick..  Broadcasting violation to other units.' </p>
<p>--You have looted a Micro Servo.-- </p>
<p>You have slain a spiderling! </p>
<p>--You have looted a Spiderling Silk.-- </p>
<p>Finkel Rardobaen tells you, 'I'll give you absolutely nothing per Micro Servo' </p>
<p>Finkel Rardobaen tells you, 'I'll give you 1 silver per Wooden Shards' </p>
<p>LOADING, PLEASE WAIT... </p>
<p>You have entered Greater Faydark. </p>
<p>Your Location is -451.03, 520.32, 116.28 </p>
<p>You say, 'Hail, Maesyn Trueshot' </p>
<p>Maesyn Trueshot says 'Welcome to Kelethin, Gnormy!  I am Maesyn Trueshot, commander of Faydark's Champions.  We are the finest marksmen in all of Norrath.  With our trusty [Trueshot longbows] we can miss no target regardless of the distance or the conditions.' </p>
<p>You say, 'what trueshot longbows' </p>
<p>Maesyn Trueshot says 'The Trueshot Longbow was created by my famed father, Eldin Trueshot. It is quite accurate and takes a ranger's skill to wield. We use our new recruits to [gather materials] needed by my father.  We shall soon begin to release the formula to good elves so all may fletch such a bow.' </p>
<p>You say, 'I will gather materials' </p>
<p>Maesyn Trueshot says 'Take this pack. Go to Kaladim, find Trantor Everhot and ask for dwarven wire. Then go to Freeport to meet Jyle Windshot. Search the inns for him and ask him for treant wood. Then, collect some spiderling silk from spiderlings and finally, in Steamfont, we have the permission of the gnomes to use any micro servos we find while destroying rogue spiders. Combine them all and return the pack to me.' </p>
<p>[in the materials pack combine:] </p>
<p>1 Dwarven Wire </p>
<p>1 Wooden Shards </p>
<p>1 Spiderling Silk </p>
<p>1 Micro Servo </p>
<p>You have fashioned the items together to create something new! </p>
<p>[non-skill Combine - No fail = pack of materials] </p>
<p>[Give Maesyn Trueshot the Pack of Materials] </p>
<p>Maesyn Trueshot says 'I shall see that my father gets the materials.  I hope this can be of use to you.  It will serve as your starting point toward fletching a Trueshot longbow.  It is unfortunate that we are unable to enchant the bow to its [next incarnation], but it is still a fine weapon. You do know the [correct components] needed for fletching such a bow, do you not?' </p>
<p>Your faction standing with Faydarks Champions got better. </p>
<p>Your faction standing with King Tearis Thex got better. </p>
<p>Your faction standing with Clerics of Tunare got better. </p>
<p>Your faction standing with Soldiers of Tunare got better. </p>
<p>Your faction standing with Crushbone Orcs got worse. </p>
<p>You gain experience!! </p>
<p>You receive 6 gold from Maesyn Trueshot. </p>
<p>[Recieve Treant Bow Staff from Maesyn Trueshot] </p>
<p>[in Fletching Kit combine:] </p>
<p>Treant Bow Staff </p>
<p>Micro Servo </p>
<p>Dwarven Wire </p>
<p>Planing Tool </p>
<p>You have fashioned the items together to create something new! </p>
<p>[Fletching combine - trival 235 = Trueshot Longbow] </p>
<p>Wooden Shards </p>
<p>Item Lore: Treant Wood Shards </p>
<p>Trueshot Longbow </p>
<p>Item Lore: Trueshot Longbow </p>
<p>The next step after the Trueshot Longbow is the Rain Caller quest which requires the Trueshot Longbow. </p>
<p>In South Felewithe in enchanters Guild - talk to Kinool Goldsinger </p>
Hail </p>
<p>Kinool Goldsinger says 'Oh, um, on second thought, never mind.  I should really just do it myself.  Thank you anyway.' </p>
<p>You say, 'where can i get an enchanted Trueshot longbow' </p>
<p>Kinool Goldsinger says 'Alas...  Another ranger in search of the [Rain Caller].  She is no more.' </p>
</p><p>
